snippet.textDisplay:
Reading through the comments its clear that this sketch went over most people’s heads.
The guys in the play don’t forget their lines. They notice the audience reactions to their lines and start going off script, competing to see who can get the bigger reaction. This keeps going until they are doing anything to get the audience to react.
Why is this funny you ask?
This is much more than about political pandering. It’s actually a very sophisticated satire on the civil rights movement, on aspects of black culture, sermons, and the penchant of leaders for soundbites and alliterative rhetoric which form part of a performance of ‘blackness’. And a satire on a supposed rivalry between Dr King and Malcolm. They then pursue this ad absurdum, until they are just shouting out black cultural cliches like Wesley Snipes quotes, doing the worm and the Moonwalk.
Only Key & Peele can get away with satire like this- skewering white culture and black culture alike. It’s so multi-layered and perfectly pitched. Best sketch writers of their generation.
